threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a backdoor that provides remote shell access. It achieves persistence by copying itself to a filename under `/var/lock/` and creating a lock file at `/var/run/auditd.lock`. The malware evades detection by daemonizing and spoofing its process name to masquerade as legitimate system services (e.g., `/sbin/udevd`, `/sbin/auditd`). The backdoor is triggered by specific network packets, after which it can manipulate firewall rules using `iptables` and spawn a reverse shell via `/bin/sh` to grant the attacker remote control.
